The paper discusses the use of both Answer Set Programming (ASP) and Machine Learning (ML) in analyzing the evolution of neurological disorders. This suggests that the paper could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DB (Databases). However, given the focus on both logic-based reasoning and neural networks, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques is also briefly mentioned, which could place the paper in cs.CL as well. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for the framework to be applied in other scenarios, which could suggest a connection to cs.DB.
